<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,411,1050]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">
Herb 1.5–2.0 m high. Clump-forming, with 10–20 pseudostems per clump. Leafy shoot composed of ca. 17 leaves. Leaf sheaths striate, tomentose. Ligule entire, 
<quantity box="[649,741,447,474]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="5.0">5–8 mm</quantity>
long, tomentose or glabrous. Petiole 
<quantity box="[1154,1260,447,474]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="14.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="9.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="5.0">5–14 mm</quantity>
long, tomentose. Lamina lanceolate, 20–30 × 
<quantity box="[448,546,483,509]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="cm" value="8.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="7.0">7–10 cm</quantity>
, apex acute, base obtuse, lateral vein densely prominent when dry, glabrous except margins ciliate and midvein pubescent abaxially. Inflorescence panicle and cincinnate, 
<quantity box="[1122,1234,519,545]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="cm" value="25.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="20.0">20–30 cm</quantity>
long, usually 1- or 2-branched, secondary branches many and short, 
<quantity box="[701,828,555,582]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="cm" value="2.15" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2.8 cm</quantity>
long, with 4–7 bracteoles. Peduncle green, pubescent. Peduncular bract 1–2, lanceolate, 
<quantity box="[512,608,591,617]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="cm" value="12.5" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="8.0">8–17 cm</quantity>
long, brown, persistent. Fertile bract inconspicuous. Bracteole funnel-form, 
<quantity box="[136,231,627,653]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
long, scarlet when young, brown when old, apex obliquely truncate, nearly glabrous. Flowers 
<quantity box="[1324,1451,627,653]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2999999999999998" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="cm" value="1.2999999999999998" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.4 cm</quantity>
long, fleshy. Pedicel 
<quantity box="[368,461,663,689]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="2.0">2–8 mm</quantity>
long, pubescent. Calyx cupular, 
<quantity box="[825,918,663,689]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
long, scarlet, apex 3-cleft, glabrous. Floral tube 
<quantity box="[136,231,699,725]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
long. Dorsal corolla lobe elliptic, 8–10 × 
<quantity box="[718,815,699,726]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5 mm</quantity>
, mostly scarlet and sometimes pink or greenish yellow, apex obtuse, glabrous. Lateral corolla lobes oblong, 6–10 × 
<quantity box="[828,925,735,761]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
, colour and indumentum same as dorsal lobe. Labellum broadly ovate, 6–7 × 
<quantity box="[496,591,771,798]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6 mm</quantity>
long, concave, Scarlet with a bright yellow longitudinal band in the centre, two cream patches along the edges of the band, base reddish yellow, red veins radiating from near centre towards the margins, glabrous. Lateral staminodes quadrate or triangluar, 
<quantity box="[841,936,843,869]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
long, red with yellow dots, base bearing red callosities covering corolla throat, glabrous. Stamen 1.0– 
<quantity box="[783,858,879,905]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="cm" value="1.1">1.1 cm</quantity>
long. Filament slender, 
<quantity box="[1133,1227,879,905]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8 mm</quantity>
long, red abaxially, light red adaxially. Anther 
<quantity box="[439,533,915,941]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 mm</quantity>
long, light yellowish red. Epigynous glands triangular, 2.0– 
<quantity box="[1213,1299,915,942]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
long, scarlet. Ovary pyriform, bright green, glabrous. Style filiform, glabrous. Stigma elongate, ca. 
<quantity box="[1120,1222,951,978]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="0.25">0.25 mm</quantity>
wide, without cilia. Capsules ellipsoid, 1.0– 
<quantity box="[407,484,987,1013]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="cm" value="1.4">1.4 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[558,653,987,1013]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="8.0" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="7.0">7–9 mm</quantity>
wide, slightly contracted in the middle, green when young, turning to maroon when ripe, with 3–5 seeds. Seeds aromatic.
</paragraph>
